Step 4: Contact Multiple Insurance Brokers
Do NOT go directly to insurance companies yet. Instead, work with 2-3 licensed health insurance brokers who specialize in small business insurance in New Jersey. Brokers don't cost you anything (they're paid by the insurance companies) and they can:
Quote multiple carriers simultaneously
Navigate complex plan designs
Handle paperwork and enrollment
Provide ongoing support
Sometimes access better rates than going direct
Find brokers through:
National Association of Health Underwriters (NAHU) - find local members
eHealth for Small Business
Your local Chamber of Commerce recommendations
Your current general liability insurer (Hiscox) may have referrals
