Visa status and health insurance eligibility: H-1B and H-4 visa holders are FULLY eligible for employer-sponsored health insurance. There are no restrictions on this. They're treated exactly the same as US citizens or permanent residents for health insurance purposes.
US citizen child: The child being a US citizen doesn't change anything for private health insurance purposes. The child is covered under the family plan just like any other child.
